72
00:04:14,219 --> 00:04:17,240
That means, well, you know the word heated, right?

73
00:04:17,379 --> 00:04:18,920
It's to make something hot.

74
00:04:19,139 --> 00:04:20,660
But how is that different from reheated?

75
00:04:20,939 --> 00:04:23,980
Well, because you cooked it already, so it was warm.

76
00:04:24,199 --> 00:04:27,459
Now it went a little bit cold because it's at room temperature.

77
00:04:27,639 --> 00:04:36,199
So in order to make sure that it's safe to eat and you kill that bacteria, you reheat it so you kind of cook it again a little bit.

78
00:04:36,439 --> 00:04:37,199
Yeah, you cook it again.

79
00:04:37,199 --> 00:04:44,819
And so with leftovers, we often have to reheat things because they were hot, then they were cold, and now we want them hot again.

80
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:45,279
That's right.

81
00:04:45,379 --> 00:04:46,000
So we reheat them.

82
00:04:46,199 --> 00:04:48,579
The opposite of that would be refrigerate.

83
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:49,180
Right.

84
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,620
And this is what you should do.

85
00:04:50,839 --> 00:04:59,100
